# Task Definition
Create a fully functional scientific calculator as a single HTML page, utilizing JavaScript for calculations, with a focus on accessibility, input validation, and error handling.

# Requirements

## HTML Structure:
- Design a clean and simple interface with buttons for digits (0-9), operations (+, -, *, /, sin, cos, tan, etc.), and a display area.
- Include accessibility features for better user experience, such as ARIA attributes for screen readers.

## JavaScript Logic:
- Implement calculations using the eval() function, while ensuring input validation to prevent the evaluation of illegal expressions.
- Use event listeners for buttons to capture clicks and handle input.

## Input Handling:
- Allow users to enter expressions for calculations.
- Provide buttons for clearing the display and starting a new calculation.

## Error Handling:
- Display an error message for invalid expressions.
- Prevent the calculator from crashing on invalid inputs.
- Example Output: The calculator should be able to handle basic arithmetic operations and trigonometric functions.

## Implementation Guidelines
- Use a modular approach for JavaScript code organization.
- Ensure all event listeners are properly removed when components are updated or replaced.
- Validate user input on each key press to prevent invalid characters.
- Implement a mechanism to handle and display errors gracefully.

## Code Structure
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Scientific Calculator</title>
    <style>
        /* Basic styling for accessibility and layout */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        {
            width: 300px;
            margin: auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #f0f0f0;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        button {
            width: 60px;
            height: 40px;
            margin: 5px;
            font-size: 16px;
        }
        #display {
            width: 100%;
            height: 40px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            font-size: 24px;
            text-align: right;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px;
            background: #fff;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="calculator">
        <input type="text" id="display" placeholder="0" aria-label="Calculator display" readonly>
        <div>
            <button onclick="clearDisplay()">C</button>
            <button onclick="backspace()">DEL</button>
        </div>
        <div>
            <button onclick="appendInput('7')">7</button>
            <button onclick="appendInput('8')">8</button>
            <button onclick="appendInput('9')">9</button>
            <button onclick="appendInput('/')">/</button>
        </div>
        <div>
            <button onclick="appendInput('4')">4</button>
            <button onclick="appendInput('5')">5</button>
            <button onclick="appendInput('6')">6</button>
            <button onclick="appendInput('*')">*</button>
        </div>
        <div>
            <button onclick="appendInput('1')">1</button>
            <button onclick="appendInput('2')">2</button>
            <button onclick="appendInput('3')">3</button>
            <button onclick="appendInput('-')">-</button>
        </div>
        <div>
            <button onclick="appendInput('0')">0</button>
            <button onclick="appendInput('.')">.</button>
            <button onclick="calculate()">=</button>
            <button onclick="appendInput('+')">+</button>
        </div>
        <div>
            <button onclick="appendInput('sin')">sin</button>
            <button onclick="appendInput('cos')">cos</button>
            <button onclick="appendInput('tan')">tan</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        let currentInput = '';

        function appendInput(value) {
            currentInput += value;
            document.getElementById('display').value = currentInput;
        }

        function clearDisplay() {
            currentInput = '';
            document.getElementById('display').value = '';
        }

        function backspace() {
            currentInput = currentInput.slice(0, -1);
            document.getElementById('display').value = currentInput;
        }

        function calculate() {
            try {
                const result = eval(currentInput);
                document.getElementById('display').value = result;
                currentInput = result.toString();
            } catch (error) {
                document.getElementById('display').value = 'Error!';
                currentInput = '';
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
